question: Olivia has 14 jars of sprinkles in her storage room. Each jar of sprinkles can decorate 16 cookies. Olivia wants to bake enough cookies to use up all of her sprinkles. If each tray holds 7 cookies, how many trays worth of cookies should she bake?
answer:
She has enough sprinkles for 14 * 16 = <<14*16=224>>224 cookies.
She needs 224 / 7 = <<224/7=32>>32 trays to bake all of the cookies.
#### 32
